summary: Canvas - Discussion on Explainable AI  [DBM140 Embodying intelligent behavior in social context]
description:
Description: One experimental paper on explainable AI will be assigned to each group. In addition, (at least one) review paper on the same topic is provided to everyone.  The experimental paper gives a case study, while the review paper provides general knowledge on the subject.

For the second meeting of Week 2, you need to upload a presentation to summarize the experimental paper assigned to your group, focusing on:

* the problem motivation,

* the role of AI and the learning algorithm,

* the role and application of XAI -- if not applicable: can XAI improve the interaction and how?

* identify limitations of the study and proposed improvements focusing on the role of (X)AI.

One person per group should be ready to present these slides to all students and teachers. All students should be prepared to discuss the quality of this solution (using the conclusions from the review paper(s) you read).

description:
Description: The Personal Development Plan (PDP) is a tool to support your development. It is a document for planning and directing your competency development on a continuous level, by formulating goals based on your reflection on learning experiences. Formulating goals provides your learning with a direction and makes it possible to evaluate and monitor your progress.

The idea is that you use the PDP as a tool to direct your long-term (vision on designing, what kind of designer you want to become) and short-term development (what do you want to achieve per learning activity). Therefore, you write/adjust your PDP before each teacher coach/mentor meeting in which your study planning and future career is addressed.

A PDP is not a fixed document; you change it along with your development. You are expected to upload your document - with the possibility to update your document multiple times during the semester. Always upload a final version before the indicated deadline on Canvas.  

Please upload the Personal Development Plan (pdf-A format) in this assignment.

Please name your plan in the following manner; M22_PDP_Last name_Initials.pdf
Replacing the red text with your own last name, initials and project title.

You can find more information on the content of the PDP on our [Online Education Guide.] (https://educationguide.tue.nl/programs/graduate-school/masters-programs/industrial-design/learning-at-industrial-design/self-directed-learning/personal-development-plan)

description:
Description: Filling out an ERB form is mandatory for student projects in certain situations:

* Is the data you want to collect explorative or not? See [this document] (https://canvas.tue.nl/courses/25207/files/4985059?wrap=1) to help guide you. If the data you want to collect is explorative, you do not need to fill out an ERB form. Should the set up of your project change, you might still need an ERB approval. 

* In any other circumstances, please fill out the ERB form.
Please see below for further details:

Step 1
Please fill out the [ERB form] (https://canvas.tue.nl/courses/25207/files/5003945?wrap=1) and discuss the form with your graduation mentor. Together you can finetune the form. You can use the minimal risk [checklist ] (https://canvas.tue.nl/courses/25207/files/4931778?wrap=1)and [this page] (https://educationguide.tue.nl/programs/graduate-school/masters-programs/industrial-design/regulations/scientific-conduct/ethical-review) as guidelines.
If you or your graduation mentor have questions please contact [ID.erb@tue.nl] (mailto:ID.erb@tue.nl).

Step 2
Once your graduation mentor has signed the form, you (the student) should email the form to [ethics@tue.nl] (mailto:ethics@tue.nl).

Step 3

If your project is within minimal risk you will receive a confirmation from the ethics team.

In this assignment upload:
1) the confirmation letter/email
2) the signed ERB form

If your project is not within minimal risk the ethics team will inform you and your graduation mentor, and forward your form to the local or central ERB. You will be informed if your project has been approved as soon as possible.

In this assignment upload:
1) the approval letter/email from the ERB
2) the signed ERB form

Please note: You are not allowed to start your work with participants (people) before you have completed this process.
